rush with the eerie, horrific, and uncanny.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 4aArchaeology. 4aArt and Material Culture. 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aSociology and Social History. 7aART / History / Renaissance.2bisacsh  aShipwrecks, maritime archaeology, archaeological theory, art theory, ontology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074322708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048543823zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048543823423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048543823/original  a978-3-11-074322-7  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK